### LLM API Test Suite
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code to run these requests
###
### For Local LLM (DeepSeek-Coder V2) tests:
### 1. Make sure Ollama is running: ollama serve
### 2. Pull the model: ollama pull deepseek-coder:latest
### 3. Set LLM_BACKEND=local in your environment (or use backend: "local" in request)
###
### Note: The API automatically detects if you're running locally vs in Docker
### and will try localhost as fallback if the configured URL fails

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@contentType = application/json

### Variables
@topic = Python programming
@level = medium
@nQuestions = 2
@language = en

###############################################
### Health Check
###############################################

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###############################################
### Question Generation Tests
###############################################

### Generate Questions - Basic (OpenAI default)
POST {{baseUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "topic": "{{topic}}",
  "level": "{{level}}",
  "n_questions": {{nQuestions}},
  "language": "{{language}}"
}

### Generate Questions - Easy Level
POST {{baseUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "topic": "JavaScript basics",
  "level": "easy",
  "n_questions": 1,
  "language": "en"
}

